"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-andy-murray-says-goodbye-to-tennis-at-the-2024-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Andy Murray\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s professional competitive career came to a close at the2024 Paris Olympics, after a storied run with his doubles partner, Daniel Evans. Representing Great Britain, the two compatriots saved match points in their final two games, keeping hope alive for one last magical run at the sport that has given Murray his greatest glory.  The two-time gold medalist, 37, was\\u00c2\\u00a0hoping to add another gold, this time in doubles. He and Evans had played inspiring tennis, coming from behind in two three-set thrillers in the round of 32 and 16. But in the quarters against Americans Taylor Fritz and Tommy Paul, their luck ran out, going out in two sets, 6-2, 6-4.  Still, the Great Scot left his emotions on the clay courts of Roland Garros, inspiring tennis fans to keep rooting for the impassioned player.  It's raining in Paris \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u00ba#Tennis@andy_murraypic.twitter.com/oCvPtlP5W6  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI knew that moment was coming for the last few months,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Murray said after the loss in doubles,according to theNew York Post. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf it didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t happen today, that was going to be in a couple days\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 time, and I was ready for it. Obviously, I was emotional because it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the last time I will play a competitive match. But I am genuinely happy, just now. I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m happy with how it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s finished.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Murray is a three-time Grand Slam title holder and former No. 1 player in the world. But it's his title as two-timeOlympic gold medalistthat the Scottish pro holds sway over his great rivals Roger Federer, Rafael Nadal and Novak Djokovic. Murray is the only tennis player to hold two gold medals in singles.  He won gold at the London Games in 2012. He then followed with an unprecedented repeat at the 2016 Rio Games. Only Serena and Venus Williams own more gold medals in tennis.  Murray announced that his retirement was official in the only way that he could:  Never even liked tennis anyway.  Lots of tributes poured in, of course, including his great rival Federer, who he beat at the 2012 London Games to avenge his loss to the Swiss at Wimbledon the month before. Both matches were played at the SW19.  Roger with nothing but respect and admiration for#SirAndy\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0092\\u0099@rogerfederer|@andy_murraypic.twitter.com/VEYsHv4RmS  Nadal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094who is also possiblycontemplating his own retirement\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094paid tribute to Murray.  All the memories, all the moments shared... \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u00ba@RafaelNadalreminisces on his time with@andy_murray\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0099\\u008c#SirAndypic.twitter.com/kngf2xyUFa  Djokovic\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094who just made the Olympics final for the first time in his career\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094also sent his support.  A legend honours a legend \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u008f@DjokerNolehas a special message for@andy_murray\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f#SirAndypic.twitter.com/Z7cZrDAGhH  Murray followed up his mic drop tweet with a heartfelt thank you to his fans.  \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00a7\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00b2 A message to you from@andy_murray\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u00a5@TeamGBpic.twitter.com/LXrBskUaKI  Murray won his first Grand Slam title against Djokovic at the 2012U.S. Openin a five-set thriller. In 2013, the Glasgow native became the first British man to win Wimbledon in almost 80 years. It was no small task, having to face down Djokovic again in the final, which he won in three sets. He repeated the feat three years later, in 2016, again in three, this time against Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Milos Raonic.  But it was 2016 that was a remarkable year for the three-time major winner. Murray reached his tennis zenith with the world No. 1 ranking, a Masters 1,000 title, Olympic gold in singles, a second Wimbledon title and the ATP Finals championship. No other tennis player has realized all of that in one year.  But the 2016 achievements also took a toll on Murray\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s physicality, beginning a streak of injuries that he never really recovered from.  It's possible that Murray suffered the most during the Golden Era of Tennis, when he often had to go up against some of the best players the sport has ever seen: Federer, Nadal and Djokovic (to be a true list you would have to include Rod Laver, in my opinion). It is a testament to Murray\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s drive that he accomplished so much during that time. His iconic back-to-back golds in singles puts him in a category all his own.  Wimbledon posted a tribute to the Scotsman, who represented so much pride for the U.K. They had held a celebratory ceremony for Murray at this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tournament.  A story we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll never tire of reliving.Andy Murray\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s#Wimbledonjourney - in his own words \\u00e2\\u009c\\u00a8pic.twitter.com/WjKZvoBfVo  A very warm welcome for a very special person. \\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008fAndy Murray received a guard of honour from Team GB as he arrived back.  \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u009d#Paris2024#BBCOlympicspic.twitter.com/iBUA5PDRH0  It was a privilege to share the court with you, Andy! \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u00b9\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0099\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u00bb Congratulations on a legendary career and for being an example to all. You will always have a fan here! \\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f@andy_murray\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00b8 Gettypic.twitter.com/QCNRERPMIw  Congratulations@andy_murrayon an amazing career! You gave it everything, and never left a stone unturned. Enjoy your retirement and look forward to a game of golf soon! \\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u00be \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ac\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00a7pic.twitter.com/vybgONpBhe  An emotional end to an incredible career \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u00b9Always an inspiration, Laureus Award winner@Andy_Murrayretires as true legend of the sport.#Olympics|#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/aSBrbHKkUd  What\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s next for the philanthropic Sir Andy Murray?According to his wife, she says she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be happy to have him home, since she \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cneeds help with the children.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d They have four.  The All England Lawn and Tennis Club will also dedicate the Centre Court in Sir Andy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s honor.  The LTA has announced that The Queen\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Club Centre Court is going to be renamed Andy Murray Arena.Incredible \\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008fpic.twitter.com/V7tbUJZ4Hv  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026Minute Media-All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Minute Media or its affiliates and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"